# Manifold Markets REST API — Manual Test Requests
# --------------------------------------------------
# Requires: VS Code REST Client extension (Huachao Mao)
#
# Auth: set MANIFOLD_API_KEY in the root .env file.
# Format: "Key <token>" — NOT Bearer.
# Most GET endpoints work without auth; auth gives access to private markets.
#
# NOTE: API domain moved from manifold.markets/api to api.manifold.markets.
#       The codebase default is already correct.
#
# Docs: https://docs.manifold.markets/api

@baseUrl  = https://api.manifold.markets/v0
@apiKey   = {{$dotenv MANIFOLD_API_KEY}}
@username = jeremiahbuckley

# ============================================================
# USER — run these first to get your userId, needed for market filters
# ============================================================

### Get authenticated user — confirms your API key works, returns your userId
GET {{baseUrl}}/me
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get user by username — public, no auth needed
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/{{username}}
Accept: application/json

###

# ============================================================
# MARKETS — list and browse
# ============================================================

### Browse markets — most recent, no auth
# Valid sort values: created-time (default), updated-time, last-bet-time, last-comment-time
# Valid order values: asc, desc (default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/markets?limit=20&sort=created-time&order=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### Browse markets — filter by creator userId
# Get your userId from GET /me above, then paste it here
@userId = YOUR_USER_ID_HERE

GET {{baseUrl}}/markets?userId={{userId}}&limit=20
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Browse markets — filter by groupId (topic)
# Get a groupId from GET /group/[slug] below, then paste it here
@groupId = YOUR_GROUP_ID_HERE


GET {{baseUrl}}/markets?groupId={{groupId}}&limit=20
Accept: application/json

###

### Search markets — filter by topic slug (the right way to filter by topic)
# topicSlug is the slug from the group/topic URL, e.g. "us-politics", "ai"
# filter values: all (default), open, closed, resolved, news, closing-week, closing-month
GET {{baseUrl}}/search-markets?topicSlug=us-politics&filter=open&contractType=BINARY&limit=20
Accept: application/json

###

### Search markets — filter by creator (using creatorId, not username)
# Get creatorId (= userId) from GET /user/[username] above
GET {{baseUrl}}/search-markets?creatorId={{userId}}&sort=newest&limit=20
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Search markets — full-text search with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/search-markets?term=2026+election&sort=most-popular&filter=open&contractType=BINARY&limit=20
Accept: application/json

###

# ============================================================
# SINGLE MARKET
# ============================================================

### Get market by ID — includes answers for multi-choice markets
@marketId = YOUR_MARKET_ID_HERE

GET {{baseUrl}}/market/{{marketId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get market by slug — slug is the URL path after the username
@marketSlug = will-there-be-a-us-recession-in-2026


GET {{baseUrl}}/slug/{{marketSlug}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get current probability for a market
GET {{baseUrl}}/market/{{marketId}}/prob
Accept: application/json

###

# ============================================================
# TOPICS (groups)
# ============================================================

### Get topic by slug — use this to find a groupId for market filtering
@topicSlug = us-politics

GET {{baseUrl}}/group/{{topicSlug}}
Accept: application/json

###

# ============================================================
# BETS (user trade history)
# ============================================================
#
# KNOWN LIMITATION: bets return a contractId, but there is no
# GET /v0/contract/[id] endpoint. For binary markets, contractId == marketId
# so GET /v0/market/[contractId] works directly. For multi-choice markets,
# contractId is an answer-level contract ID, not the top-level market ID,
# so that lookup will fail.
#
# Two workarounds:
#
#   Option A — Direct lookup (binary markets only):
#     Take the contractId from a bet and call GET /v0/market/[contractId].
#     Works for YES/NO markets. Fails for multi-choice answer bets.
#
#   Option B — Bulk scan (all market types):
#     1. Call GET /v0/markets (paginate with &before=) to fetch all markets.
#     2. Each market has an id and, for multi-choice, answers with their own ids.
#     3. Build a map: contractId → market.
#     4. Join bets to markets using that map.
#
#   Option C — Positions instead of raw bets (recommended for market context):
#     GET /v0/get-user-contract-metrics-with-contracts returns your aggregate
#     positions AND the full market objects in one response. No join needed.
#     Use this when you want to see which markets you've bet on, not the
#     individual trade-by-trade history.

### Get bets — all bets, most recent first
# Each bet: id, contractId, amount, outcome, probBefore, probAfter, createdTime
GET {{baseUrl}}/bets?username={{username}}&limit=100
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get bets — paginate using before=<bet_id> from previous response
GET {{baseUrl}}/bets?username={{username}}&limit=100&before=LAST_BET_ID
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get bets for a specific market (once you have the contractId/marketId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/bets?username={{username}}&contractId={{marketId}}&limit=100
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Option A — look up a market directly by contractId (binary markets only)
# Paste a contractId from the bets response above
@contractId = PASTE_CONTRACT_ID_FROM_BET_HERE

GET {{baseUrl}}/market/{{contractId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Option B — fetch all markets for bulk matching (page 1)
# Note the id of the last market in the response, then use it as &before= below
GET {{baseUrl}}/markets?limit=1000&sort=created-time&order=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### Option B — fetch all markets (next page)
# Paste the id of the last market from the previous response
GET {{baseUrl}}/markets?limit=1000&sort=created-time&order=desc&before=LAST_MARKET_ID
Accept: application/json

###

# ============================================================
# PORTFOLIO (Option C — positions with market context included)
# ============================================================

### Get user portfolio metrics — live balance, profit, invested value
GET {{baseUrl}}/get-user-portfolio?userId={{userId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get positions with full market objects — best way to see market context
# Returns { metricsByContract: { contractId: [ContractMetric] }, contracts: [market] }
# No join required — market data is embedded alongside your position metrics.
# userId and limit are both required. order: lastBetTime (default) or profit
GET {{baseUrl}}/get-user-contract-metrics-with-contracts?userId={{userId}}&limit=50&order=profit
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###

### Get positions — next page
GET {{baseUrl}}/get-user-contract-metrics-with-contracts?userId={{userId}}&limit=50&order=profit&offset=50
Authorization: Key {{apiKey}}
Accept: application/json

###
